<h2>Portfolio Sharing Process</h2>

<h3>Hub Account Actions</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Create portfolio in hub account</li>
  <li>Add products to the portfolio</li>
  <li>Create portfolio share to target accounts or organization</li>
  <li>Configure sharing permissions and access controls</li>
</ol>

<h3>Spoke Account Actions</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Accept the portfolio share from hub account</li>
  <li>Configure local access permissions</li>
  <li>Associate principals (users, roles, groups) with imported portfolio</li>
  <li>Begin using shared products for launches</li>
</ol>

<h2>Access Control and Permissions</h2>

<h3>Hub Account Permissions</h3>
<p>The hub account needs permissions to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Create and manage portfolios</li>
  <li>Create portfolio shares</li>
  <li>Manage product associations</li>
  <li>Update sharing configurations</li>
</ul>

<h3>Spoke Account Permissions</h3>
<p>Spoke accounts need permissions to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Accept portfolio shares</li>
  <li>List shared portfolios</li>
  <li>Associate principals with imported portfolios</li>
  <li>Launch products from imported portfolios</li>
</ul>

<h2>Portfolio Lifecycle Management</h2>

<h3>Initial Sharing</h3>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Hub account shares portfolio
aws servicecatalog create-portfolio-share \
  --portfolio-id port-abc123def456 \
  --account-id 987654321098 \
  --share-principals

# Spoke account accepts share  
aws servicecatalog accept-portfolio-share \
  --portfolio-id port-abc123def456 \
  --accept-language en
</code></pre>

<h3>Managing Shared Products</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Hub account controls product availability</li>
  <li>Product updates automatically propagate to spoke accounts</li>
  <li>Hub account can revoke access to specific products</li>
  <li>Spoke accounts see real-time product catalog updates</li>
</ul>

<h3>Share Termination</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Hub account can terminate portfolio shares</li>
  <li>Spoke accounts lose access to shared products</li>
  <li>Existing provisioned products may continue to run</li>
  <li>New launches from shared products are blocked</li>
</ul>

<h2>Principal Association</h2>

<h3>User Access</h3>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">imported-portfolios:
  development-tools:
    portfolio: DevelopmentToolsPortfolio
    hub_account_id: "123456789012"
    principals:
      - type: user
        name: developer-user-1
      - type: group  
        name: development-team
    deploy_to:
      tags:
        - regions: us-east-1
          accounts:
            - "987654321098"
</code></pre>

<h3>Role-Based Access</h3>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">imported-portfolios:
  admin-tools:
    portfolio: AdminToolsPortfolio
    hub_account_id: "123456789012"
    principals:
      - type: role
        arn: "arn:aws:iam::987654321098:role/ServiceCatalogAdminRole"
      - type: role
        arn: "arn:aws:iam::987654321098:role/InfrastructureRole"
    deploy_to:
      tags:
        - regions: us-east-1
          accounts:
            - "987654321098"
</code></pre>

<h2>Best Practices</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Plan your hub-and-spoke architecture carefully</li>
  <li>Use organizational sharing for enterprise-wide services</li>
  <li>Implement least-privilege access for portfolio principals</li>
  <li>Document shared portfolio purposes and intended audiences</li>
  <li>Monitor portfolio usage and access patterns</li>
  <li>Regular review of sharing permissions and access</li>
  <li>Version control portfolio configurations</li>
